text: Pico Mágina is a mountain in Spain. == Geography == The mountain is located in Jaén Province, in the northern part of the autonomous community of Andalusia. It's the highest peak of the province and also of Sierra Mágina, and is located on the border between the municipalities of Albanchez de Mágina and Huelma. geodesic vertex (2,164 masl) and endpoint of his climb path. == Access to the summit == The summit can be accessed by hiking trails. The walk up to the summit is quite long: the first part follows a dirt road and the last one a hiking path through rocky terrain. == Nature conservation == The mountain and most of its chain are included from 1989 in the Parque Natural de Sierra Mágina.Parque Natural de Sierra Mágina ==See also== *Baetic System ==References== ==External links== * Route to Pico Mágina from A-324 road Huelma-Cambil on www.jaenparaisointerior.es Category:Baetic System Category:Mountains of Andalusia Category:Geography of the Province of Jaén (Spain) Category:Two-thousanders of Spain
